# ⭐ Band 8 Sample Answer

## Introduction

The bar chart illustrates the results of a survey on the proportions of residents in five Australian cities who bought fresh coffee, bought instant coffee, or visited a café for coffee or tea in the previous four weeks.

**翻译：**
该柱状图展示了一项调查结果，内容是澳大利亚五个城市中居民在过去四周内购买现磨咖啡、速溶咖啡或前往咖啡馆喝咖啡或茶的比例。

---

## Overview

Overall, visiting cafés was the most popular choice in most cities, particularly in Melbourne and Hobart, whereas buying fresh coffee was generally the least common activity. In addition, instant coffee was consistently more popular than fresh coffee across all cities.

**翻译：**
总体来看，在大多数城市中，去咖啡馆是最受欢迎的选择，尤其是在墨尔本和霍巴特，而购买现磨咖啡通常是最不常见的。此外，在所有城市中，速溶咖啡的受欢迎程度始终高于现磨咖啡。

---

## Body Paragraph 1

In terms of visiting cafés, Melbourne recorded the highest proportion at approximately 65%, followed closely by Hobart at around 64%. Sydney and Brisbane also showed relatively high figures, at about 61% and 55% respectively, while Adelaide had the lowest rate at just over 50%.

**翻译：**
在去咖啡馆方面，墨尔本的比例最高，约为65%，紧随其后的是霍巴特，约为64%。悉尼和布里斯班的比例也较高，分别约为61%和55%，而阿德莱德最低，仅略高于50%。

---

## Body Paragraph 2

Regarding coffee purchases, buying instant coffee was more common than fresh coffee in every city. Hobart had the highest percentage for instant coffee at around 60%, whereas Brisbane and Adelaide followed at roughly 55%. By contrast, the figures for fresh coffee were lower overall, with Sydney and Melbourne at about 43–44%, and Brisbane showing the lowest proportion at approximately 34%.

**翻译：**
在咖啡购买方面，所有城市中速溶咖啡都比现磨咖啡更受欢迎。霍巴特的速溶咖啡比例最高，约为60%，而布里斯班和阿德莱德约为55%。相比之下，现磨咖啡的比例整体较低，悉尼和墨尔本约为43%至44%，布里斯班最低，约为34%。

